WEBVTT

00:01.058 --> 00:04.562
This sermon is brought to you by Beaufort Road Baptist Church.

00:05.042 --> 00:07.785
The speaker today is Pastor Tony Kahoot.

00:09.828 --> 00:15.194
All right, tonight we want to get going and we want to pick up where we left off last Wednesday night.

00:16.295 --> 00:20.279
And I'm going to ask you to turn with me to Revelation chapter 10.

00:20.339 --> 00:23.623
And we're going to pick up tonight with verse number seven.

00:24.684 --> 00:29.970
And we actually were mentioning a few of the things that

00:30.242 --> 00:42.727
Verse 7 talks about, I think it would be appropriate for us to go back and re-enterate where we were and where we left off and pick up there in a very more orderly fashion.

00:43.388 --> 00:47.316
So I want to read for you in Revelation 10, beginning in verse 7.

00:48.318 --> 00:52.306
But in the days of the voice of the seventh angel,

00:54.530 --> 00:58.716
when he shall begin to sound the mystery of God.

00:58.837 --> 01:01.861
And so I want you to underline that phrase, the mystery of God.

01:01.941 --> 01:10.394
Let me say this, there are some things about the Bible we will never understand in this life.

01:12.457 --> 01:23.314
No matter how much we study, no matter how much we use references, commentaries, there are things that we're just not going to be able to get.

01:23.426 --> 01:25.168
we're not going to be able to understand it.

01:26.149 --> 01:35.301
And God reference these kinds of things as the mysteries of God, and we will see in other places.

01:36.502 --> 01:41.008
But I think that there are things that we can know.

01:41.028 --> 01:52.402
There are things that are reserved for us not to know the fanalities of these particularities until we get on the other side.

01:52.674 --> 01:59.864
But here's the thing that I believe is the personal conviction it might not be yours and God bless you so forth, Hallelujah.

01:59.884 --> 02:20.573
But I believe this that some of the things that we find so mind boggling and it seems like this, just a big hoop for us to jump through and we just can't connect the dots and it's frustrating and we do everything we can and we still come back to the place.

02:20.633 --> 02:21.554
I just don't get it.

02:22.306 --> 02:23.047
Here's the thing.

02:24.168 --> 02:28.694
And you might say, you know, the first thing I'm going to do when I see Jesus, I'm going to ask you about this thing.

02:28.754 --> 02:31.818
I just couldn't get down there on his life in this earth.

02:32.479 --> 02:46.738
But I really believe this, that when we get to heaven, whether it be by death or rapture, and we see those nail scarred hands and we see his nail scarred feet.

02:48.898 --> 02:52.581
and we like Thomas can put our hands on his ribbon side.

02:55.244 --> 02:59.448
I don't believe we will give the things down on this life a second thought.

03:01.530 --> 03:05.734
We will embrace the Savior and it will not be a matter of importance to us now.

03:07.375 --> 03:18.866
When we've been there 10,000 years, bright shining as the sun, somewhere along the millionth year, you might pull Peter, James, and John to the side and say, hey, man, connect these dots.

03:19.330 --> 03:20.292
And that will be okay.

03:21.754 --> 03:32.373
But, you know, the thing is, I don't believe that when we get to heaven and see the Lord that we're going to rush Him and we're going to beg Him to tell us about the things we didn't understand in this life.

03:32.393 --> 03:35.379
There are some things we just won't know in this life.

03:36.541 --> 03:40.227
And as the song says, we'll understand it better in the by and by.

03:40.267 --> 03:43.433
Maybe He will give us a full discourse of those things.

03:43.473 --> 03:44.114
I don't know.

03:45.666 --> 03:52.176
But I have come to find out this, that there are things when I do reach a place that I don't understand.

03:52.276 --> 03:53.437
I do give it my best.

03:54.078 --> 03:56.021
I study, I search the scriptures.

03:56.802 --> 03:58.024
I do all that I can.

03:58.044 --> 04:03.813
And there are occasions when I come to a place where I just don't know.

04:04.934 --> 04:12.786
And this is what I have found out to be helpful to me, and I think beneficial for you.

04:13.506 --> 04:23.559
And that is this, that when I get to such a place, it's best for me and beneficial for you, for me to tell you, I just don't know.

04:25.142 --> 04:29.748
Rather than me try to make up something for you to just get a little chill or a goosebumps.

04:29.768 --> 04:32.251
Listen, that's not what this is all about.

04:32.271 --> 04:34.895
There are some things I will never know.

04:37.097 --> 04:43.506
Because of that, my responsibility to teach and preach the Word of God, I might be shallow in a truth here or a truth there.

04:45.122 --> 04:49.368
I will tell you one thing I'm absolutely sure on, and that is Jesus is the only way to heaven.

04:51.170 --> 04:55.797
And there is no other way to be saved, no other name given among men, whereby we must be saved.

04:55.837 --> 04:59.602
I can promise you I'm dead sure of that.

04:59.622 --> 05:06.151
So when we get to a place like this, the mystery of God, there are several.

05:06.431 --> 05:07.613
I'm going to give you seven.

05:08.153 --> 05:10.737
I gave you a few of them last Wednesday night.

05:10.757 --> 05:14.482
Should be finished as he hath declared to his servants,

05:15.138 --> 05:17.601
the prophets.

05:17.621 --> 05:24.968
Now, when I get to this place, the mystery of God, I want to list for you seven, which the Bible speaks about.

05:25.028 --> 05:28.973
I gave you last Wednesday night, the mystery of God's will.

05:29.774 --> 05:33.457
And I gave you the reference in Ephesians chapter one and verse number nine.

05:33.497 --> 05:41.586
And so if you were writing those down, or we seem to have been going so fast that you missed it, we give it to you again tonight.

05:41.890 --> 05:49.498
heaven, may known unto us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure, which he had purposed in his heart.

05:50.259 --> 05:52.722
Then we talked about the mystery of iniquity.

05:53.542 --> 06:00.830
And the Apostle Paul was writing in 2 Thessalonians, chapter 2, verse number 7, for the mystery of iniquity.

06:01.771 --> 06:03.413
That's already working only he.

06:03.813 --> 06:06.857
This is what we spend a lot of time with last Wednesday night.

06:06.957 --> 06:08.178
He the Holy Spirit

06:08.482 --> 06:11.446
who now leteth, will let until he be taken out of the way.

06:11.506 --> 06:13.549
