06:21.380 --> 06:23.142
The word says this.

06:24.624 --> 06:28.810
And without controversy, great is the mystery of godliness.

06:29.991 --> 06:37.682
God was manifest in the flesh justified in the spirit scene of angels preached unto the Gentiles, believed on in the world.

06:38.434 --> 06:40.636
received up in glory.

06:41.277 --> 06:44.961
Now, let me say a word about the mystery of godliness.

06:45.882 --> 06:51.668
I think all of us know what it is to live a godly Christian life.

06:51.928 --> 07:01.238
We know what it's like to live in an exemplary way where we listen, be careful.

07:01.879 --> 07:04.882
We cannot be perfect and we cannot live above sin.

07:05.858 --> 07:08.322
It's the same thing like Mary, the mother of Jesus.

07:10.044 --> 07:11.927
She was not blessed above women.

07:12.868 --> 07:14.551
She was blessed among women.

07:15.652 --> 07:21.721
And none of us, no matter how long we have been saved, we will never reach sinless perfection in this life.

07:21.781 --> 07:26.247
Some people teach it, some people preach it, and it's a doctrine that some people adhere to.

07:27.669 --> 07:30.834
We will never be able to reach sinless perfection.

07:31.586 --> 07:34.190
That's why 1 John 1 9 is in the Bible.

07:34.250 --> 07:41.120
If we confess our sins, He is faithful and just to forgive us of our sins and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

07:42.002 --> 07:49.292
Now, because we cannot live perfect, that has a consequence on every aspect of our life.

07:49.373 --> 07:50.735
We will make bad decisions.

07:51.856 --> 07:53.018
We will have bad thoughts.

07:55.101 --> 07:56.784
Perhaps we will go to bad places.

07:59.548 --> 08:01.010
A lot of things in our life

08:01.314 --> 08:06.943
really hinge on our depravity, our humanity.

08:09.527 --> 08:17.741
But it comes down to a lot of times when I have students from the school who get themselves in a wad.

08:19.263 --> 08:24.212
I have to sit down and talk to them in love.

08:25.754 --> 08:28.178
And one of the things I helped them to

08:28.322 --> 08:34.791
admit and come face to face with and that is that they do have the ability to know the difference between right and wrong.

08:36.853 --> 08:39.477
And so that's not an issue for us.

08:39.557 --> 08:47.548
We do know even unbelievers have a conscience and know the difference between right and wrong.

08:48.969 --> 08:55.378
But what the lost does not have is the convicting power of the Holy Spirit.

08:57.474 --> 09:10.010
So as a believer, listen, when we get ourselves in a mess, the spirit, and even really before we get into the mess, I think the Holy Spirit gives us complete conviction.

09:10.070 --> 09:11.372
You better not do this.

09:11.492 --> 09:13.214
You better think this through.

09:13.274 --> 09:14.396
You better not go there.

09:14.476 --> 09:16.619
You better not say that and get involved with this.

09:17.159 --> 09:25.330
And so sometimes we have the warnings, but we don't heat them and we just press through and we end up suffering the consequences.

09:25.730 --> 09:27.253
We know what Godliness is.

09:27.713 --> 09:39.434
I don't want any of us to think that there is a place, a plateau where we can arrive and achieve to where we are going to be sinless and perfected in this life that's not going to happen.

09:41.858 --> 09:48.850
We will not be perfect until we receive a glorified body, and that glorified body is not given to us until the Rapture.

09:50.050 --> 09:56.097
The Bible says that when the rapture take place that we will see him and we shall be like him.

09:56.217 --> 10:01.322
We will be perfected in a glorified body on the day of the rapture and not before.

10:02.263 --> 10:03.685
So let me say this.

10:05.247 --> 10:09.712
He who is without sin, throw the first stone.

10:12.795 --> 10:15.718
I've learned a long time ago not to carry rocks in my pocket.

10:18.121 --> 10:19.282
I can assure you that.

10:20.034 --> 10:29.826
But I think we do know what godliness is all about, what wholeness is all about.

10:29.866 --> 10:40.799
Now, we don't have to walk around dressed like monks and use the words, brother of how art thou, and we don't have to put on some kind of cosmetic charade.

10:43.523 --> 10:44.744
But this is what I believe.

10:46.847 --> 10:49.650
Jesus said, let your light so shine before me.

10:53.282 --> 10:54.584
He said, you're the light of the world.

10:54.724 --> 10:56.246
Now that's a big responsibility.

10:57.948 --> 11:02.713
All of us have a responsibility to be the light of the world, salt of the earth.

11:02.733 --> 11:06.478
So I think that there's a little bit more light on this.

11:06.578 --> 11:08.621
Now let me give you this one, the mystery of God.

11:08.781 --> 11:23.058
Colossians chapter two and verse number two, that their hearts might be comforted being knit together in love and unto all riches of the full assurance of understanding to the acknowledgment of the mystery of God.

11:24.802 --> 11:27.244
and of the Father and of Christ.

11:28.546 --> 11:41.738
