24:21.579 --> 24:22.740
And I wish I were them.

24:23.161 --> 24:26.684
And I wish I had what they had and didn't have to go through what I listen.

24:28.186 --> 24:33.692
We are all of us are beautifully and wonderfully, uniquely, each league made.

24:34.753 --> 24:38.137
And we are all made different in the image of God.

24:39.378 --> 24:43.963
So the correct way to read the verse is exactly what it says.

24:44.263 --> 24:46.866
And we know that all things work together.

24:49.634 --> 24:52.297
Now, who's good?

24:54.479 --> 24:57.903
It doesn't say, and we know that all things work together for our good.

25:00.565 --> 25:05.030
As a believer, we have to understand that everything is working together for God.

25:07.192 --> 25:09.294
We know that all things work together for good.

25:09.515 --> 25:16.722
God's glory to them that love God, to them who are called according to His purpose.

25:16.962 --> 25:20.106
So we have to remember that God has a master plan for all of us.

25:21.508 --> 25:31.883
In Acts chapter 15 and verse number 18, the word says this, known unto God are all His works from the beginning of the world.

25:32.063 --> 25:35.107
So God has a master plan for each of us.

25:35.708 --> 25:42.898
So when we read verse number seven, having said everything we've just said since the beginning of the study tonight, let me read it.

25:43.522 --> 25:54.954
But in the days of the voice of the seventh angel, when he shall begin to sound the mystery of God, it should be finished as he hath declared to his servants the prophets.

25:54.974 --> 25:56.416
Now we move to verse number eight.

25:57.978 --> 26:12.914
And the voice which I heard from heaven speak unto me again and said, go and take the little book, which is open in the hand of the angel, which standeth upon the sea and upon the earth.

26:13.410 --> 26:19.417
Now, John's being instructed here to take the book out of the hand of the mighty angel.

26:19.517 --> 26:22.680
And he does that in verse number nine.

26:23.541 --> 26:28.987
And I went unto the angel and said unto him, give me the little book.

26:30.669 --> 26:33.772
And he said unto me, take it.

26:33.792 --> 26:42.021
Now, here is a mysterious verse.

26:42.041 --> 26:42.962
The angel said,

26:43.490 --> 26:51.058
Take it, but then here's something we don't understand and eat it.

26:53.581 --> 27:10.098
Take it and eat it up and it shall make thy belly bitter, but it shall be in thy mouth sweet as honey.

27:10.498 --> 27:12.802
John is commanded to eat this book.

27:13.122 --> 27:13.904
Wow.

27:14.925 --> 27:22.398
So in verse 10, and I took John says, we'll close here tonight with this, and I took the little book out of the angel's hand.

27:22.558 --> 27:24.261
And I did exactly what I was told.

27:24.361 --> 27:24.842
I ate it.

27:25.904 --> 27:26.625
I ate it up.

27:28.027 --> 27:30.171
And it was in my mouth, sweet as hunting.

27:31.653 --> 27:35.620
And as soon as I had eaten it, my belly was bitter.

27:36.661 --> 27:37.042
So

27:37.474 --> 27:42.240
He does what he's told, and it becomes sweet in his mouth, bitter in his belly.

27:42.800 --> 27:49.948
And so the message of this comes down to grace and redemption, I believe.

27:50.829 --> 27:58.558
The message of grace, the message of redemption and peace is sweet.

27:58.578 --> 28:01.682
But God's judgment is better.

28:05.858 --> 28:07.840
And John said, I've got to deliver this.

28:08.702 --> 28:12.707
Now I don't have time to get into some subpoints tonight and some additional verses.

28:12.787 --> 28:14.028
Lord willing to pick up here.

28:14.048 --> 28:18.153
